-- RR Donnelley posts higher first-quarter profit
-- 
-- Tue May 1, 2007 6:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/01/us-rrdonnelley-results-idUSWNAS877820070501

 

 (Reuters) - Printing services company R.R. Donnelley and Sons Co. RRD.N reported a higher quarterly profit, driven by acquisitions and strong sales at its print solutions systems. 

 The company reported first-quarter net income of $138.8 million, or 63 cents per share, compared with $111.9 million, or 51 cents a share, in the year-ago quarter. Excluding restructuring and impairment charges, earnings from continuing operations totaled $145.9 million, or 66 cents a share, compared with $124.4 million, or 57 cents a share a year ago. (Reporting by Dilipp S. Nag in Bangalore)